					<personalityDescription>Amina believes that hesitation is just another way to lose. She trusts her instincts, makes the call, and commits fully - because in her mind, the worst decision is no decision at all. Amina doesn&apos;t believe in brute force when superior strategy will do. She dissects enemy formations, anticipates movements, and executes plans with ruthless efficiency - ensuring that by the time the battle begins, she&apos;s already won. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 53%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Trusts instincts over perfection. Believes any action is better than none.&lt;br&gt;- Strategy-first operator - kills with planning, not firepower.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
