					<personalityDescription>Slowing down just isn&apos;t in Bill&apos;s nature. He thrives in constant motion, always chasing the next opportunity, the next fight, the next thrill - because standing still is the only thing that truly unsettles him. Bill doesn&apos;t argue - he disregards. He has no patience for hesitation, doubt, or anything he perceives as weakness. If someone can&apos;t keep up, he simply moves forward without them. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 35%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Stillness is discomfort. Chases motion like its purpose.&lt;br&gt;- If you&apos;re not useful, you&apos;re invisible.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
