					<personalityDescription>Hieronim is content with where he is. While others scramble for promotions, glory, or power, he sees no reason to stress - he does his job, collects his pay, and doesn&apos;t bother chasing dreams that require unnecessary effort. No matter how hardened the universe tries to make him, Hieronim refuses to shut himself off from others. He carries their burdens as if they were his own, always willing to stand beside those who feel lost or alone. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 34%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Clock-puncher. No fire, no hunger, no ambition.&lt;br&gt;- Doesn&apos;t harden - chooses to feel. Risky, but admirable.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
