					<personalityDescription>Younes puts in the work, no matter how long it takes. Whether it&apos;s maintaining their combat unit, planning battle strategies, or honing their skills, they refuse to cut corners - because in their mind, effort is what separates the competent from the dead. Younes doesn&apos;t believe in partial effort because they&apos;ve seen how easily things fall apart. The almost-finished defenses that didn&apos;t hold. The half-prepared plans that led to disaster. They either do things fully, or they don&apos;t do them at all - because anything in between is just waiting for disaster to happen. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 45%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Puts in the hours. Refuses shortcuts - effort equals survival.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
