					<personalityDescription>Gisselle doesn&apos;t believe in limits. Whether it&apos;s effort, firepower, or sheer presence, she always pushes past what&apos;s necessary, turning every task into something grander, louder, and more overwhelming than it has to be. Gisselle&apos;s knee bounces when she&apos;s on a stakeout. Her hands tap rhythms when she&apos;s waiting to drop. Her fingers drum against her sidearm before a fight. Some say it&apos;s nerves, some say it&apos;s a bad habit - but whatever it is, it&apos;s impossible to ignore. Her lance isn&apos;t sure if it makes her more dangerous, or if one day, she&apos;s just going to snap. </personalityDescription>
