					<personalityDescription>Torsten carries an insatiable hunger for destruction, his mind always drawn to the raw power of things being pushed past their limits. There is no satisfaction in stability - only in the knowledge that something, somewhere, is being torn apart. Torsten has seen too many commanders make grand speeches, give bold promises - only to watch them die meaningless deaths. He doesn&apos;t inspire with words. He inspires by surviving, by acting, by doing what has to be done without the need for reassurance. Those who follow him don&apos;t do it because he tells them to. They do it because he keeps them alive. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 63%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Only satisfied when things are breaking. Craves instability.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
