					<personalityDescription>Wouter doesn&apos;t waste time on emotions or sentiment - only results matter. He makes hard choices without hesitation, cutting losses when needed and sacrificing whatever is necessary to secure long-term success. Wouter used to care, used to feel. But war doesn&apos;t care, and eventually, he learned to stop wasting energy on emotions no one had time for. If something&apos;s wrong, he fixes it. If something hurts, he pushes through it. &quot;Pain means you&apos;re still alive. That&apos;s all it means.&quot; </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 50%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Cold logic, no heart. Cuts losses like dead limbs.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
