					<personalityDescription>Annabelle isn&apos;t interested in quick victories - she&apos;s interested in certain victories. She waits, watches, and maneuvers every piece into place before making her move, ensuring that when the moment comes, her enemies never see it coming. Annabelle doesn&apos;t just explain - she over-explains everything, because if she keeps talking, if she keeps analyzing, then she doesn&apos;t have to think about the bigger picture. The bodies. The losses. The inevitable end. If she stops, she&apos;ll have to face it all at once. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 55%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Prefers certainty to speed. Strikes only when the board is set.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
