					<personalityDescription>Maria-Wilhelmina doesn&apos;t hesitate when faced with the impossible - She meets it head-on, with a steady gaze and an unshakable will. She knows that fear is inevitable, but surrender is a choice. Even in the heat of war, Maria-Wilhelmina never loses sight of the people fighting beside her. Whether it&apos;s sharing supplies, covering for a comrade&apos;s mistake, or simply checking in, she proves that true leadership starts with empathy. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 44%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Faces the impossible with level focus. Fear acknowledged, never obeyed.&lt;br&gt;- Leads with empathy. The kind we need more of.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
