					<personalityDescription>Abdelwahab knows exactly what to say to get people on his side, but his words rarely match his true intentions. He smiles, flatters, and makes promises, but beneath it all, he&apos;s only looking out for himself. In the chaos of war, Abdelwahab keeps one thing constant. Maybe it&apos;s a trinket from home, maybe it&apos;s something given to him by someone long gone. It doesn&apos;t matter what it is - what matters is that it&apos;s his. When the battle&apos;s over and the adrenaline fades, he he grips it tight, reminding himself that he&apos;s still here. </personalityDescription>
					<personalityInterviewNotes>&lt;html&gt;&lt;b&gt;Performance Exam:&lt;/b&gt; 55%&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- All charm, no substance. Says the right things, means none of them.&lt;/html&gt;</personalityInterviewNotes>
